    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                <head>No. 715.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Polo
                                        de Bernabe</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 3,
                                        1874</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of
                                Spain, while having the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the note
                                of the honorable Secretary of State of the United States, of the 22d
                                of December last, in which it is declared that the Virginius at the
                                time of her capture had no right to carry the American flag, and did
                                carry it wrongfully and improperly, must express to the Secretary of
                                State the satisfaction with which the government of the Spanish
                                Republic has been informed of this declaration, and that this
                                result, which was confidently expected, practically demonstrates
                                that there was no offense to the American flag, and that no
                                intention to insult it ever could or ever did exist.</p>
                <p>The undersigned avails himself of this opportunity to reiterate to
                                the Hon. Hamilton Fish the assurance of his highest
                                consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOSÉ POLO DE BERNABÉ.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
